  "narrative": {
    "intro": "In FY2026 to date, federal contract obligations in Delaware totaled $142M. Obligations were down 61.4% year over year while buyers awarded 2,499 contracts at an average award size of $56.8K. The current-year total is partial (fiscal year to date) and reflects activity through the reporting period. Recent fiscal-year comparisons show wide swings in annual obligations, with prior-year fiscal totals including $321M in FY21, $81.3M in FY22, $325M in FY23, $337M in FY24, and $368M in FY25, highlighting that FY2026 to date sits below several recent full-year totals.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What drove federal obligations in Delaware in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense accounted for the largest share with $60.1M in obligations. The Department of Veterans Affairs followed with $30.5M and the Department of Health and Human Services with $16.1M. Combined, these three agencies represent a substantial portion of the $142M total."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors dominate Delaware federal contracting?",
        "body": "Top buying agencies by obligations include the Department of Homeland Security at $8.5M, the Department of Justice at $6.5M, and the Department of Labor at $5.1M, among others through the top ten list. Leading vendors in FY2026 to date are AQUIA NAVA II LLC at $11.8M, CORBALT, LLC at $10.8M, and STONEWIN INTERNATIONAL, LLC at $10.1M. Major industries receiving obligations include Other Computer Related Services at $17.7M and Custom Computer Programming Services at $10.9M."
      }
    ]
  },
